title: Aufstand gegen Adolf Hitler! - It Happened on July 20 [1955] war
description:
Es geschah am 20. Juli (1955 - West Germany)       It Happened on July 20th
                                                   aka Aufstand gegen Adolf Hitler!
                                                   aka Jackboot Mutiny

Drama / History / Thriller / War

director . . . . Georg Wilhelm Pabst
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0048040/


Filmed at Coburg and Munich, Bavaria, Germany

Colonel Baron Schenk von Stauffenberg made an attempt to kill Hitler using a bomb at his "Fuehrer headquarters" in eastern Prussia. Georg Pabst has reconstructed events up to the colonel's court martial and execution chronologically and in a meticulous way, demonstrating an honest effort to be precise regarding historical facts. With considerable detail, and employing an excellent cast, he relates what really happened on that day. Much of the dialogue is lifted straight from historical records, and there are no fictional characters added.


Video: DivX5, 640x480, 25.000 fps, 1500 Kbps, 01h14m25s
Audio: MP3, 44100 Hz, joint stereo, 96 kbps

DVDRip, German audio, optional subtitles English and Spanish
